  { year: 2024, label: `Testing Ground`, narrative: `This year tested the community as much as it rewarded it. Home foundations were laid in April, but May also brought an elephant that tore through the original mud hut's structure — even as new water-harvesting earthworks began nearby. September's downpour undid years of repair work, washing out the very same bund the community had first lost back in 2017. Still, the year closed on warmer notes: a November meet-up with filmmaker Sumanth Kuduvalli, and the fourth edition of 3Bs&1H with naturalist Deepa Mohan in December.`, events: [
    { month: 'Apr', title: `Foundations laid for the first homes`, type: 'ochre', text: `Foundation work began for the community's first homes.`, images: ['/images/journey/journey-27.jpg'] },
    { month: 'May', title: `Annual gathering at Good Earth Malhar`, type: 'neutral', text: `The May city meet-up was held at Good Earth Malhar.`, images: ['/images/journey/journey-28.jpg'] },
    { month: 'May', title: `An elephant damages the mud hut`, type: 'ember', text: `An elephant searching for food destroyed the structure surrounding the original mud hut.`, images: ['/images/journey/journey-29.jpg'] },
    { month: 'May', title: `Earthworks begin for water harvesting`, type: 'water', text: `New earthworks got underway for capturing and harvesting water on site.`, images: ['/images/journey/journey-30.jpg'] },
